<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Arrives in Ukraine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
arrived here today for a 24-hour visit to Ukraine where he is
expected to sign a landmark friendship treaty between the two
former Soviet republics.
</P>
<P>
The first official visit to Ukraine by Yeltsin would be "the
most complex one, as well as the president's most important
foreign policy action this year," Russian presidential spokesman
Sergei Yastrzhembsky said in Moscow today, reports said.
</P>
<P>
Upon their arrival, Yeltsin and his wife Naina were greeted by
Ukrainian Prime Minister Pavlo Lazarenko.
</P>
<P>
On Saturday, Yeltsin and his Ukrainian counterpart, Leonid
Kuchma, are to sign the friendship and cooperation treaty.
</P>
<P>
Kiev and Moscow initialed the friendship treaty two years ago,
but Yeltsin postponed his visit to Ukraine to its signing six
times, because of disputes over the Black Sea Fleet and its bases
on Crimea.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, the premiers of the two countries entered
agreement on the fleet and its bases, paving the way for the visit
and the pact. 
</P>
</TEXT>
