<HEADLINE> Eight Handicapped Killed in Fire in Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Eight mentally handicapped people were
killed and nine others injured when a fire swept through a home
run by the Protestant church in eastern German city of Frankfurt
on the Oder, local reports said.
</P>
<P>
The blaze broke out at about 11 p.m. Thursday at the back of
the home in the center of the city which is on the Polish border.
</P>
<P>
Fire fighters said about 90 of the home's 145 residents were
evacuated and taken to hospital with breathing problems. One of
the injured was still in critical condition.
</P>
<P>
The rescue operation was difficult because many of the
residents were too disabled to walk or bedridden. Many others
panicked and were unable to help themselves, reports said.
</P>
<P>
Police said the cause of the fire was still unknown, but arson
was not suspected. 
</P>
</TEXT>
