<HEADLINE> Metals Turnover Hits 89 Million Tons in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Turnover at the Shanghai Metals
Exchange surpassed 89 million tons worth 1.9 trillion yuan (229
billion US dollars) in the past five years, according to official
statistics.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Metals Exchange is now China's largest futures
market for non-ferrous metals.
</P>
<P>
Average annual transaction at the Shanghai exchange equals five
times the country's annual metal output since it was founded in
1992. The exchange's total turnover accounted for 70 percent of
the national total in the five years.
</P>
<P>
The number of exchange members has jumped from 43 to 120. Its
clients now number more than 3,400, including the Baoshan Steel
Corporation, one of China's largest iron and steel works.
</P>
<P>
Approximately 30 large copper and aluminium producing
enterprises in China are registered at the Shanghai exchange, with
their combined registered output of copper and aluminium making up
80 percent and 50 percent of the national total.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the exchange has also formed a complete set of
risk-controls, according to an exchange official.  
</P>
</TEXT>
