<HEADLINE> More Funds Pumped into Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Investors are pouring more into
stock market oriented mutual funds in May, helping boost the stock
rally.
</P>
<P>
Cash flows to mutual funds have gained strength in the last two
months -- with inflows to stock funds reported at 15.7 billion
U.S. dollars in April, up from 10.75 billion U.S. dollars in
March.
</P>
<P>
For the first four months of the year, investors put 73.73
billion U.S. dollars into stock funds, down from 98.6 billion U.S.
dollars at year earlier.
</P>
<P>
Researchers put the funds inflow in May at an estimated 19
billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Bond funds had inflows of 786.1 million U.S. dollars, swinging
from an outflow of 2.01 billion U.S. dollars in March.
</P>
<P>
The local newspapers reported here today that with the fund
injection and other helpful economic data, the Dow Jones
industrial average is up more than 15 percent since April 11.
</P>
<P>
The technology laden Nasdaq composite rose 11 percent in May.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
