<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stock Index Hits New High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Hang Seng Index, the key
indicator of Hong Kong's blue chips, closed at a record high of
14,757 points today.
</P>
<P>
It was the second time in a week that the Index smashed
records. Total turnover on Friday reached 18.73 billion HK dollars
(2.4 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Property and finance led the blue chips higher in today's
transactions. The properties sub-indices rocketed 635 points in a
single day, while the finance sub-indices surged 497 points. Other
two sub-indices for commerce and industry, and utilities also
increased by a big margin.
</P>
<P>
Securities analysts said that a bullish sentiment surrounding
the handover would continue to dominate the market in the coming
weeks.
</P>
<P>
On the first trading day of this week, the Index surged up to
14,574 points and recorded the highest single-day turnover of
20.58 billion HK dollars (2.6 billion US dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
