<HEADLINE> Radio Play on Macao Basic Law to Be on Air </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, May 30 (Xinhua) -- A 13-part radio play promoting the
Basic Law of Macao will be on air twice a week starting from June
13, organizers said today.
</P>
<P>
The radio play, which depicts three brothers' life experience
in Macao's transition period before its return to China in 1999,
will be broadcast by the Chinese channel of Radio Macao at noon
and evening every Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Each part of the play, including interviews with legal experts
and hotline questions and answers, will last 25 minutes.
</P>
<P>
"We try to focus on one or two topics in each part, like 'Macao
people governing Macao', 'a high degree of autonomy' and 'basic
life style and the capitalist system remaining unchanged by
2049,'" said Annabella Choi Chi Ieng, chief of the Chinese channel
of Radio Macao, at a press conference today.
</P>
<P>
Legal experts who participated in the drafting of the Basic Law
will be invited to give briefing on certain topics.
</P>
<P>
The promotion of the basic law remains constant in Macao.
Various activities, including lectures, contests, booklets and
postcards, have been adopted.
</P>
<P>
"It is the common wish of all Macao residents to see a smooth
handover and a stable transition in Macao," said Lau Cheok Va,
deputy secretary-general of the Macao Basic Law Promotion
Association. "We will continue our efforts in the future. We hope
the law would be properly implemented."  
</P>
</TEXT>
