<HEADLINE> Swedish Sprint Wins 13th Stage of Giro d'Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Swedish racer Glenn Magnusson clinched
the 13th stage of the Giro d'Italia cycling race on Friday,
holding off Italian Mario Cipollini's quest for a record fifth win.
</P>
<P>
Magnusson opened a gap in the last 300 meters, then looked
around before raising his arms in triumph as Mirko Rossato beat
compatriot Cipollini for second place in the 145-km stage from
Varazze to Cuneo.
</P>
<P>
Russian Pavel Tonkov, safely tucked away in the massed sprint
at the finish, still holds his overall lead of 41 seconds over
Frenchman Luc Leblanc. 
</P>
