<HEADLINE> Chinese Duo Enter Mixed Doubles Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GLASGOW, Scotland, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese duo Liu Yong and
Ge Fei beat Michael Sogaard and Rikke Olsen of Denmark in straight
sets on Friday to enter the mixed doubles final of the world
badminton championships here.
</P>
<P>
Liu and Ge, who beat the Danish pair in a quarter-final on
their way to All England Open title this March, had to overcome a
0-7 first-game deficit to snatch 15-10, 15-9 victory.
</P>
<P>
The fourth-seeded pair has won all four events they competed
since their formation early this year.
</P>
<P>
In Saturday's final, they will meet Denmark's Jens Eriksen and
Marlene Thomsen, who rallied from one-set down to upset top-seeded
Trikus Heryanto and Minarti Timur of Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
Eriksen and Thomsen, who beat the Indonesians twice at Korea
Open and Japan Open this year, lost the first game 18-15 but
managed to come back to win the second game 15-13.
</P>
<P>
The two pairs tied at 11-all, 12-all and 14-all in the third
game before going to the four-point setting, which the Danes
clinched 4-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
