<HEADLINE> OAU to Take Measures to Deter Military Takeover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, May 30 (Xinhua) -- A committee set up by the Organisation
of African Unity (OAU) Mechanism for Conflict Prevention, Management
and Resolution is drawing a list of measures to be adopted by
African states in the event of any military takeover of a legitimate
civilian government.
</P>
<P>
OAU spokesman Ibrahim Dagash said here today the committee,
chaired by Gabon, was expected to recommend measures that would deter
coups.
</P>
<P>
In the past the OAU merely condemned military coups without
taking preemptive action due to the organisation's policy of
non-interference in internal affairs of sovereign states.
</P>
<P>
But since the establishment of the peace-making organ in 1992 the
OAU has increasingly been involved in internal conflicts.
</P>
<P>
Dagash said, ''we have to talk to these military governments to
persuade them to return to democratic rule. We have to speak to
them.''
</P>
<P>
He added, ''the OAU also feels that Nigeria is a big country and
what happens there affects other countries. That is why we did not
want to hurry the process of democracy and lead to a fragile
arrangement.''
</P>
<P>
He said the committee's recommenations would be tabled before the
OAU's peace-making organ for adoption and implementation. enditem

