<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Secures 1-2-3 Finish in Women's Singles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GLASGOW, Scotland, May 30 (Xinhua) -- China showed its
dominating power in women's singles when Gong Zhichao and Wang
Chen ousted the last Indonesians hopes Susi Susanti and Mia Audina
to establish all-Chinese semi-finals at the world championships
here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
All-England runner-up Gong beat former world champion and fifth
seed Susanti 11-5, 11-2 in just 24 minutes while world junior
champion Wang had an equally easy 11-6, 11-4 win over third-seeded
Audina in 29 minutes.
</P>
<P>
"I am older than my opponent and I am now married," said
Susanti after her second loss in two months to the Chinese
teenager since All England Open this March.
</P>
<P>
"She will follow my steps to the titles," she said of the
rising star.
</P>
<P>
In the semi-finals, Gong will face Zhang Ning or Han Jingna
while Wang is to face defending champion Ye Zhaoying or Dai Yun.
</P>
