<HEADLINE> Real Estate Booming in Guangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, capital city of
south China's Guangdong Province, saw a 17 percent rise in its real
estate investment during the first quarter this year, compared with
the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
About 758,000 square meters of housing had been pre-sold during
the three-month period, a nearly 74 percent rise over the same
period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Residential construction has become a favorite investment
choice in Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
The city's investment in the real estate rose from nearly 1.6
billion yuan in 1991 to more than 23 billion yuan in 1996,
</P>
<P>
However, the price for common residential housing is
substantially beyond the local's residents' purchasing power. And
the supply of office buildings, stores and shops has surpassed the
city's demand.
</P>
<P>
Last year, 150,000 square meters of office buildings and
160,000 square meters of shops and stores remained vacant.
</P>
