<HEADLINE> Tourism Booming in Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The city of Dandong has turned
out to be a popular tourist resort on the Sino-Korean border by
providing tourist programs with local features.
</P>
<P>
Since most of its attractions are in the mountains, the city
has spent heavily in recent years on mountain resorts, and has
several national reserves and forest parks for tourists.
</P>
<P>
