<HEADLINE> More Foreign Ships Using East China Port </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The deep-water port at Beilun near
Ningbo in Zhejiang Province in east China has been handling an
increasing number of foreign ships because it is an ice-free port
year-round.
</P>
<P>
As China's largest bulk carrier, oil, and container terminal,
it is large enough to accommodate about any ship.
</P>
<P>
Last June, China Ocean Shipping Corporation (COSCO) started
weekly service from Beilun to the east coast of the US, and
recently, included a route to the Mediterranean.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, LITTMAS of Germany and CMA of France
opened container routes to Beilun, and set up offices there.
</P>
<P>
Recently, some US shippers have contacted port authorities in
Beilun to inquire about opening container routes to the west coast
of the US.
</P>
<P>
"The foreign shipping companies' enthusiasm for Beilun comes
from its sophisticated port conditions and its geographical
location and connection with the vast inland area of China," one
port expert commented.
</P>
<P>
In order to make itself more attractive, the port has made an
effort to improve infrastructure even more and its services.
</P>
