<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shenzhen Cooperating with Areas along with Beijing-Kowloon Railway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Shenzhen will now be able to
cooperate closely with areas along the Beijing-Kowloon Railway
line, as the first train from Beijing to Kowloon entered Hong Kong
via the north-south trunk line in mid-May.
</P>
<P>
A group of experts from local organizations, including the
Shenzhen Comprehensive Development Institute, predict that more
and closer cooperation is expected in the fields of communications
and transportation, business transfer, market and resource
development, and the use of overseas funds between Shenzhen and
the interior areas.
</P>
<P>
The experts say that Shenzhen, which has the advantages of
bordering Hong Kong and being a pioneer in China's opening-up
drive, will become a successful service center through which
overseas businessmen can invest in interior areas, especially
those along the Beijing-Kowloon line.
</P>
<P>
The city, with 12 national checkpoints of exit and entry by
sea, land and air will offer standard and efficient services in
finance, information, personnel training, and transportation and
storage.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing-Kowloon line traverses seven provinces and two
municipalities from north to south, affecting 117 million
people. The areas along the line have abundant natural resources
and great potential for economic development.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen, as a major train stop of the north-south trunk line
at its southern end, had made a use of 11.87 billion U.S. dollars
of overseas funds as of the end of 1996, including investment from
more than 130 international consortia and transnationals.
</P>
<P>
The city has so far put 2.49 billion yuan into 866 projects in
areas along the rail route, while these interior areas have also
invested 4.99 billion yuan in Shenzhen, with Beijing and Tianjin
ranking far ahead of other places in terms of investment scale.
</P>
<P>
Economic and technical cooperation between Shenzhen and
interior areas along the trunk rail line had previously been
confined only to the aspects of trade, commerce and real estate.
</P>
<P>
Interior areas had supported Shenzhen's economic expansion by
way of securing funds and providing the city with advanced
technology, qualified talent and labor, and eventually developed
themselves.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Shenzhen made advanced economic and technological
progress in these interior areas by the means of launching its own
solely-funded businesses, setting up joint ventures, and engaging
in leasing, trading of properties and takeovers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
