cities were urged today to fight against possibly more active
typhoons and tropical cyclones which often claim heavy life and
property losses in the coastal areas every year.
</P>
<P>
In a two-day national conference on typhoon control, which
ended today in Fuzhou, capital of southeast China's Fujian
Province, representatives from the country's coastal areas said
China is predicted to be battered by up to nine tropical
windstorms and typhoons this year.
</P>
<P>
According to the National Meteorological Bureau and the
National Bureau of Oceanography, the country's coastal areas,
mainly Guangdong, Fujian, Zhejiang, Jiangsu and Hainan provinces,
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, and Shanghai will be the target
of this year's disaster, which are predicted to be greater in
number and move more northward.
</P>
<P>
The conference urged these localities to consolidate the dykes
and build other flood-control facilities to minimize economic
losses.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
