<HEADLINE> Chinese Pair Liu and Ge Wins Mixed Doubles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GLASGOW, Scotland, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Liu Yong and Ge Fei
became the first Chinese mixed doubles world champions in 10
years when they beat Danes Jens Eriksen and Marlene Thomsen 2-1 at
world championships final here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Liu and Ge, who beat the Danish pair at Korea Open and Japan
Open in straight sets this year, was extended to three sets, the
first time for the Chinese since the first round at this
championships.
</P>
<P>
They won the first game 15-5 easily but was denied the match
point by Eriksen and Thomsen in the second game, where the Danes
rallied from 12-14 down to draw 14-14 before winning the setting
3-2.
</P>
<P>
In the third game, Liu and Ge were never trailed to win 15-4
under a vocal support from their teammates and local Chinese
students at Scotstoun Leisure Center.
</P>
<P>
The last time a Chinese pair won the event was in 1987, when
Wang Pengren and Shi Fangjing took the crown in Beijing world
championships in China.
