<DOCNO> XIE19970531.0087 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hukou Waterfall, Renowned Scenic Spot in Northwestern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HUKOU, May 31 (Xinhua) -- A ten-year effort for comprehensive
development has turned a unique waterfall on the Yellow River into
one of northwestern China's most renowned scenic spots.
</P>
<P>
The Hukou Waterfall, situated between Shanxi and Shaanxi
Provinces, has a drop of more than 30 meters and is the only
yellow-colored waterfall in the world.
</P>
<P>
More than 20 million yuan (2.4 million US dollars) has been
used to develop the tourism resources at the Hukou falls since
1988, when it was listed as one of the country's state-level
scenic beauties.
</P>
<P>
The landscape also has, since 1994, been included on the list
of attractions for the country's tourism-promotion campaign "Visit
China '97."
</P>
<P>
Shanxi Province's Jixian County, located near the waterfall,
takes the advantage of the falls to host an international tourism
festival each year. The county alone received a total of 136,000
domestic and overseas tourists last year and earned 760,000 yuan
(95,600 US dollars) in foreign exchange.
</P>
<P>
Work on infrastructure construction in tourism zones adjacent
the waterfall is nearly completed, boosting the growth of the
local tourism industry.  
</P>
