<HEADLINE> Rural and Urban Consuming Gap to Narrow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Narrowing the gap between rural and
urban consumer goods is one of the major trends in China this year,
market analysts say.
</P>
<P>
The forecast is that urban sales will decrease while rural
sales increase, with a gap of about two percentage points, while
overall sales of consumer goods are expected to rise by about 20
percent in China.
</P>
<P>
However, overall supply will still exceed demand and problems
in the supply structure will still remain.
</P>
<P>
Consumers are expected to mature psychologically this year,
which will contribute to fewer fluctuations in the market, the
experts believe.
</P>
<P>
While cars and houses are hardly expected to become the focus
of consumers this year, the demand for telephones, air
conditioners, microwave ovens, wide-screen TVs, and VCD players
are expected to continue to rise.
</P>
<P>
Market competition is also expected to become more fierce and the
growth of privately-owned and other forms of commercial outlets
will exceed that of state- and collectively-owned commercial
enterprises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
