<DOCNO> XIE19970531.0090 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Growing Technology to Help Boost Grain Output </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, May 31 (Xinhua) -- China is increasing the use of
plastic sheeting as a technique to improve wheat growth and to
sustain agricultural development, according to a recent meeting in
Lanzhou.
</P>
<P>
Agronomists of the Academy of Agricultural Sciences in Gansu
Province started using the technology in 1992. The new technology
increased per-unit output by more than 30 percent, saving from 900
to 1,500 cubic meters of water per hectare, and increasing
farmers' income by 1,500 yuan per ha.
</P>
<P>
China has been successful with cotton and corn growing using
plastic sheeting, which saves water and is drought-resistant, and
especially suited to the particular type of farming in dry
northern China.
</P>
<P>
If the technology is applied to 3.3 million ha to 6.6 million
ha of the 11.33 million ha of spring and winter wheat land in north
China, the country can expect five to ten billion kg more in wheat
output, accounting for one-third to two-thirds of the national
target for grain output during the Ninth Five-Year Plan, experts
say. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
