recreational and residential area after all the Vietnamese boat
people held there are evacuated.
</P>
<P>
A water sports center, hotels, parks, playgrounds and
residential buildings will be built on the site which is encircled
by sea and trees, as it was described in an ambitious
redevelopment blueprint unveiled Friday by the Planning
Department.
</P>
<P>
Today's Hong Kong Standard reported that the plan would convert
20 hectares of Whitehead plus a nearby village and outlying
farmland.
</P>
<P>
The detention camp, now holding 1,581 Vietnamese boat people,
is due to close on June 30 when Hong Kong returns to China.
</P>
<P>
The report said the development plan was in its preliminary
stage and construction details had not been finished.  
