prosecuted for violating traffic rules and the amount of fine
realized from them were also more than those in the corresponding
period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The number of people prosecuted in the first four months was
48,547 and the DMP collected over 5 million taka (about 125,000
U.S. dollars) as fine for violation of traffic rules over the same
period, the sources added.  
