<HEADLINE> Unidentified Gunmen Kill 10 People in Mogadishu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Ten people were killed and six
others were wounded Thursday night when a civilian lorry was
ambushed by unidentified gunmen at Tihsile Village, 60 km south
of the capital.
</P>
<P>
The lorry transporting rice, flour and vegetables and
passengers had left Qoryoley district on its way to Baidoa Town.
</P>
<P>
Eyewitnesses said the lorry was attacked by two Japan made
Toyota pick up tracks occupied by heavily armed gunmen.
</P>
<P>
The victims include a mother and her three children aging
between one and eight years, three other women and four men while
the wounded were taken back to Afgoie Town for treatment.
</P>
<P>
The area between Afgoie Town, 30 km south of Mogadishu, and
Balidogle Airport accommodates the wildest hooligans who
continuously attack the civilian and commercial vehicles. The
gunmen who are usually equipped with hand grenades and assault
rifles erect road blocks and start shooting as soon as a vehicles
comes closer.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a large demonstration was staged today by the
school teachers in front of the offices of the World Food Program
(WFP) of the united nations in both sides of the war-torn
Mogadishu. The teachers were protesting against the WFP for not
offering them their food for work ration for the last 18 months.
</P>
</TEXT>
