<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Gets 3.57 Billion Dollar Export Earnings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh's export earnings rose to
3,574.4 million dollars during the July-April period of the
current fiscal ending June this year, according to a latest
information available from the Export Promotion Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The export earning target for the whole fiscal year had been
fixed at 4,380 million dollars. This means that an earning to the
amount of 805.6 million dollars has to be ensured to fulfill the
target.
</P>
<P>
During the 10-month period of the current fiscal year, the
price index of Bangladesh goods increased 1.97 percent compared to
that in the corresponding period of the previous fiscal year and
the volume of export increased 10.91 percent.
</P>
<P>
The export of readymade garments during the July-April period
fetched 1,764.62 million dollars, 7.93 percent less than the
target fixed for the period.
</P>
<P>
However, knitwear fetched 633.23 million dollars against the
target of 425 million dollars set for the period while the earning
from the export of frozen food (including shrimps) was recorded at
267.23 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
During the same period, export of about 107.25 million square
feet of leather (crust/finished) fetched 157.66 million dollars,
1,454.49 thousand bales of raw jute fetched 96.20 million dollars
and 421.09 thousand tons of jute products 270.16 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
As in the past, the United States was the biggest buyer of
Bangladeshi products. It was followed by the United Kingdom,
Germany, France, the Netherlands, Belgium, Italy, Japan and Iran.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
