<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Half of Students in Dhaka's Middle Schools Smoke </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dhaka, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Over 50 percent students from Class
Eight to Class 12 in different educational institutions are
smokers in Bangladesh's capital city of Dhaka.
</P>
<P>
According to a survey conducted by the Consumers Association of
Bangladesh (CAB), 70 percent of the students started smoking in
contact with friends, 13 percent being inspired by the
advertisements of the cigarette companies and the rest followed
their smoking guardians.
</P>
<P>
The survey was conducted from April 9 to May 20 on 292 students
of 21 educational institutions in the capital including City
College, Azimpur Girls School, Government Laboratory High School
and Shaheed Anwara Girls College. Eighty-six percent of the
students under survey were boys and 14 percent girls.
</P>
<P>
About 72 percent of the smokers smoke regularly and 28 percent
were casual smokers, said the survey released here today, adding
that 84 percent of the smokers have smoking friends.
</P>
<P>
Sixty-one percent of the student smokers are aware that 2.5
million people in the world die due to smoking every year, the
survey added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
