<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items in
leading French newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- The result of the second round of the French legislative
elections to be held on Sunday is hard to predict because of the
large number of voters who abstained in the first round and those
wavering between the center-right coalition and the National
Front, plus a close run in the first round between the left
parties and the center-right coalition in many constituencies.
</P>
<P>
-- Russia and Ukraine will sign a treaty of friendship today in
Kiev to mark a historic reconciliation between the two neighboring
countries. The treaty, which will put an end to the dispute
between Moscow and Kiev over the ownership of the Black Sea Fleet,
indicates the intention of President Boris Yeltsin to establish a
peaceful international environment for economic reform in Russia.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- Two days before the holding of the second round of
legislative elections, all the personnel from the French
center-right coalition have warned voters against the danger of a
cohabitation, or sharing of power, between the right and the
left. They are counting on those who abstained in the first round
of the voting and those who voted for the National Front to
support the center-right coalition in the second round.
</P>
<P>
-- In Afghanistan, the Islamic extremist movement of Taliban
has suffered several setbacks from the troops of Commander Ahmed
Shah Massoud in one week. The soldiers of Massoud are now marching
toward Kabul, while former President Burhanuddin Rabbani has
returned to the country from exile. 
</P>
</TEXT>
