<HEADLINE> Tanzania's Exports Increase Last Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania's exports amounted
to 762 million US Dollars in 1996, an increase of 11.6 percent as
compared to 1995, Minister of State Nassoro Malocho said at the
Finance and Economic Affairs Committee meeting of parliament
yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Trade deficit greatly went down last year as a result of the
increase in exports.
</P>
<P>
He said that exports in 1996 were able to finance 56 percent
of the nation's import bill for that year. "This is an
improvement over the 1995 performance, when exports were able to
finance 49 percent of the nation's import bill," he added.
</P>
<P>
Malocho said in the past, the country's exports managed to
finance hardly a third of the nation's import bill.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a pre-budget briefing session of the committee,
Malocho said that the country registered a modest 4.2 percent
economic growth last year, which is a slight increase over the
1995 growth of 4.0 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Minister, however, said the 1996 growth rate is below the
target set at 5.0 percent.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the agricultural sector, which accounted for
52.3 percent of the country's Gross domestic Product (GDP) in
1996, grew only 3.9 percent last year as against to 5.8 percent
in 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
