<HEADLINE> Dhaka Stock Exchange Ends Week Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The Dhaka Stock Exchange (DSE) ended
the trading week on last Thursday registering 29.84 point rise in
the price index.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark DSE index stood at 1,216.68 at the week's closing
over the previous week's balance of 1,187.84 points.
</P>
<P>
On the first trading day of the week on Sunday, the index
reached at 1,228.30 due to dominance trading of the gaining issues
but declined to 1,213.88 on Monday. The index again rose on
Tuesday and posted a steady growth till the closing of the week'
trading when most of the traded issues gained.
</P>
<P>
During the period, Raspit Food, Shampur Sugar, Amam Sea Food
and Delta Life Insurance were the major gainers while Chittagong
Cement Clinker, Islamic Bank, Dhaka Fisheries and Beximco
Pharmaceuticals incurred marginal losses.
</P>
<P>
A record number of issues changed hands last trading week.
Among the listed 212 securities, 141 were transacted on Thursday
which was highest ever this year in term of traded issues.
</P>
<P>
Turnover in volume and value also increased when the buyers and
sellers were active equally. On an average, about 300,000 shares
worth 90 million Taka (about 2.25 million U.S. dollars) were
traded in each day during the week.  
</P>
</TEXT>
