<HEADLINE> China's Ship Export Profitable </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Ship export has brought China 110
percent more profits during the first five months this year,
compared with that of the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics showed that China has exported ships to over
40 countries and regions in the world, and with sizable
profits. It earned 1.15 billion U.S. dollars last year for the
country, 280 million U.S. dollars more than the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Shipping industry has become mature in China which now can
design, build and repair ships with capacity of 150,000 to 300,000
tons. Some of China made ships, such as "Dalian" and "Jiangnan"
have become name brands in the world shipping market.  
</P>
</TEXT>
