<HEADLINE> Forest Zoo For Northeast China Port City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, May 31 (Xinhua) -- A forest zoo with more than 130
types of animals has opened in Dalian, a coastal city in northeast
China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The 7.2-sq.km zoo area now has more than 1,000 animals living
on its grounds.
</P>
<P>
It is divided into six functional areas including a lion and
tiger hill, a monkey garden, a bear hill, and other settings. In
addition, tourists can watch seals perform and visit a tropical
plants hall.
</P>
<P>
More than 300 people invited from overseas and China, along
with 5,000 visitors joined an opening ceremony last weekend,
sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
