<BODY>
<HEADLINE> TAZARA Ordered to Take Measures to Arrest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzania-Zambia Railway
Authority (TAZARA) Council of Ministers on Friday ordered the
authority's Board of Directors to take concrete measures to arrest
deteriorating performance, and report to the next council meeting in
September.
</P>
<P>
The ministers said the poor performance of the Chinese-built
railway line had persisted for three years and directed the board
to tighten supervision.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement issued at the end of a one-day
council meeting in Dar es Salaam, the Council of Ministers urged
TAZARA workers to work as a team irrespective of their
nationality.
</P>
<P>
A council meeting last March slated the management for
ineffectiveness, including failure to collect debts amounting to
severn million US Dollars, and ordered the board to overhaul it.
</P>
<P>
The then General Manager, Antisne Mweemba, from Zamiba was
subsequently removed by President Frederick Chiluba, and is yet to be
replaced.
</P>
<P>
