<HEADLINE> Myanmar Hails ASEAN's Decision to Admit 3 New Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar government has welcomed
the ASEAN's decision to grant Myanmar, Cambodia and Laos full
membership in July this year.
</P>
<P>
An official statement issued here today said that "Myanmar has
always placed confidence in the wisdom of the leaders of the ASEAN
member nations for the acceptance of Cambodia, Laos and Myanmar
into the prestigious association of the region."
</P>
<P>
The statement said that "the association's dream to become a
100 percent regional organization will soon become a reality, and
we all shall harmoniously work together to develop our region with
much cooperation, coordination and understanding of each other."
</P>
<P>
"Myanmar is confident that the aims and objectives of the ASEAN
shall be fully accomplished by working together unitedly under the
guidance and wisdom of the leaders of the countries in the
region," it said.
</P>
<P>
"ASEAN leaders have already proven their wisdom by successfully
 bringing in nations with different ideologies and religions
together to create a strong association in the region," it added.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN foreign ministers today decided at their special meeting
in Kuala Lumpur to admit Myanmar, Cambodia and Laos into the
regional grouping in July.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar became ASEAN's observer nation in July last year.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN now groups Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, Singapore, the
Philippines, Thailand and Vietnam.  
