SINTRA, Portugal -- Members of the Peace Implementation Council
(PIC) harshly criticized Bosnia's three-person presidency here on
Friday, and called on it to fully implement the Dayton Peace
Accords. It pointed out that proper implementation was regarded as
one of the important conditions for getting international aid. The
help that Bosnia will receive from the international community
will be dependent on the commitment it demonstrates to the peace
agreement, representatives attending PIC organized meeting said.
