All-People's Union", announced Friday that they are jointly
forming a new party, "The Union of Progressive Force." The new
party will carry out a democratic reform policy, whose main task
will be to elect a candidate in the federal and regional
elections. The party's leading group will be the coordinating
committee consisting of representatives of the three groups, with
Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin as the chairman.
