<HEADLINE> ASEAN to Admit Myanmar, Cambodia, Laos in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar, Cambodia and Laos
will be admitted into the Association of Southeast Asian Nations
(ASEAN) in July this year, Malaysian Foreign Minister Abdullah
Ahmad Badawi announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The decision to admit the three countries into the regional
grouping was made by ASEAN foreign ministers at their special
meeting held here today, Abdullah, who is currently ASEAN standing
committee chairman, told a news conference after the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was unanimous in the decision that the entry of the
three would be in July during the ASEAN Ministerial Meeting (AMM)
to be held here, he said.
</P>
<P>
The decision by the foreign ministers of the existing
seven-member ASEAN was firm and non-reversible, Abdullah said,
adding "it is a unanimous decision and there were no reservation
on the part of any ASEAN member."
</P>
<P>
ASEAN presently groups Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, Singapore,
the Philippines, Thailand and Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah said it was in the interest of the region that the
three countries were accepted into the fold.
</P>
<P>
He said when the foreign ministers made the decision they took
into consideration all aspects related to the concerned countries.
</P>
<P>
He said he will visit all the three countries soon to convey
the ASEAN decision to the leaders of these countries.  
</P>
