<HEADLINE> OAU Chief Confers With Mugabe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Secretary-General of the
Organisation of African Unity (OAU) Salim Ahmed Salim last night
conferred with the continental body's incoming chairman,
Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe on preparations for the OAU
summit due to be open here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, Salim said that he had briefed the
Zimbabwean leader on proceedings of the organization's three-day
Council of Ministers meeting just ended late last night.
</P>
<P>
''We are very satisfied with the status of the preparations,''
said Salim.
</P>
<P>
The June 2-4 OAU summit is expected to be attended by some 40
heads of state and government, including Laurent Kabila of the
Democratic Republic of Congo whose forces recently overthrew
former Zairean President Mobutu Sese Seko.
</P>
<P>
The recent crisis in the Great Lakes Region, the coup in
Sierra Leone and political developments in Somalia and Angola, as
well as the economic development in the continent are expectged
to be high on the summit's agenda. 
</P>
