<HEADLINE> Vietnam Seeks More Textile, Garment Export Markets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, May 31 (xinhua) -- Vietnam's textile and garment
enterprises are searching for more non-quota export markets,
local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The export of textiles and garments under quota to the European
Union (EU) market is estimated to reach 250 million U.S. dollars
in the first half of this year, accounting for more than 50
percent of the yearly export plan.
</P>
<P>
The implementation export quotas increased by 1.5 times
compared with the same period last year, which means that
enterprises in the textile and garment industry will meet
difficulties in ensuring jobs for their staff in the second half
of this year.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's production capacity has grown several times higher
than the annual increase of quota exports to the EU market while
the non-quota exports of textiles and garments to Japan and South
Korea have also reduced, the report added.
</P>
<P>
The enterprises, which are actively diversifying their
products, improving quality, and looking for non-quota markets,
have been warned to be careful when developing new investment
projects to keep production capacity in line with the market
demand, without solely relying on the EU market five-year export
quota agreement, which only provides an annual increase of 1 or
2 percent.
</P>
<P>
The textile and garment firms also plan to boost production of
goods for domestic consumption ensuring jobs for their workers.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
