<HEADLINE> Vietnam Bans Hunting Rare Species </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam has imposed a strict ban on
hunting 36 rare animal species including elephants, rhinoceros,
tigers, panthers, five-colored monkeys and spotted deer, local
press reported today.
</P>
<P>
According to a report from the Ministry of Agriculture and
Rural Development, some species, such as the one-horned
rhinoceros, are threatened with extinction.
</P>
<P>
There are only about eight rhinoceros of this kind remaining in
the jungles of Lam Dong Province in central Vietnam. 
</P>
</TEXT>
