<HEADLINE> Latin American Economic News Briefs (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO -- Chile's industrial output grew by 4.8 percent in
April. Industrial sales increased by 7.4 percent and electric
energy consumption by 6.1 percent, compared with the same month of
1996.
</P>
<P>
SAN JOSE -- Costa Rica expects 750,000 foreign visitors in
1997, bringing an income of 750 million dollars to the country.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Trade Ministry statistics show that the Costa Rican
tourism industry is increasing by 1.2 percent, compared with the
same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
BRASILIA -- The Brazilian harvest of grains, legumes and oil
seeds will be 78 million tons this year, a 6.74 percent increase
over last year.
</P>
<P>
The production of herbaceous cotton will be 904,000 tons, an
8.95 percent drop.
</P>
<P>
MANAGUA -- Nicaraguan tax revenue rose by 12 percent during the
first four months of this year, compared with the same period
last year.
</P>
<P>
Data from the tax authorities show that 101,000 dollars were
collected from January to April, compared with 90,000 dollars in
the same period last year. 
