<HEADLINE> New Party Established in Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Three Russian social and political
organizations announced today that they are jointly forming a new
party, "The Union of Progressive Force."
</P>
<P>
The leaders of the three parties, "Our Home is Russia",
"Reform-New policy" and "Russian All-People's Union", have signed
the agreement on establishing the new party.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the new party will be a joint organization
to carry out a democratic reform policy. Its main task will be to
elect a candidate in the federal and regional elections.
</P>
<P>
The party's leading group will be the coordinating committee
consisting of representatives of the three groups. Russian Prime
Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin will be the chairman of the committee.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin, who is also leader of the "Our Home is Russia",
said at the signing ceremony that the establishment was an
important event in Russian political life, and a crucial step in
the unifying process of Russian political forces.
</P>
<P>
The three party leaders today also issued a statement, saying
the union would struggle against any actions of extremism,
nationalism and splittism and law violations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
