<DOCNO> XIE19970531.0160 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Venezuela's Coffee Export Hits a High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Venezuela's coffee exports
increased to 632,000 quintales (30,336 tons) in the 1995-1996
export year, the highest in the last decade, a report by the
National Coffee Fund shows.
</P>
<P>
This earned 59 million U.S. dollars for the country.
</P>
<P>
The report shows that this export was a 647 percent increase
over the 1994-1995 export year's 84.500 quintales (4,056 tons).
</P>
<P>
Venezuela has 288,310 hectares (711,876 acres) cultivated with
coffee, of which 250,500 hectares (618,518 acres) are in
production, with an average yield of 6.28 quintales (301.4
kilograms) per hectare.
</P>
<P>
Venezuela is one of the major coffee exporting countries of the
world, and 96 percent of this goes to the United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
