<HEADLINE> Panamanian Police Seize Cocaine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Panamanian police seized 1,381
kilograms of cocaine and detained four suspects allegedly linked
to Colombian drug traffickers, the Technical Police said today.
</P>
<P>
Of the seized the drug, 754 kilograms were confiscated in the
Colon province and the remaining 627 kilograms in Rio Abajo, an
urban area in the capital.
</P>
<P>
The drug seized in Rio Abajo was hidden in boxes containing
electronic articles.
</P>
<P>
Police said the suspects used the Caribbean route to take the
drug to Haiti and thence to the United States.
</P>
<P>
Panama has confiscated 4,000 kilograms of cocaine this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
