<HEADLINE> Maldives to Buy More Petroleum Products from Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The Maldives has requested Sri
Lanka to supply petroleum products including jet fuel worth 31
million U.S. dollars annually.
</P>
<P>
The request was made by the Maldivian Ministry of Trade and
Industries to the Sri Lankan government at a recent trade
discussion, local newspapers reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Maldives obtained its supply of petroleum products mainly
from Singapore and Malaysia in the past years.
</P>
<P>
The Maldives began to import petroleum products from Sri Lanka
in 1990. In recent years, Sri Lanka has made significant progress
in the field of trade with the Maldives.
</P>
<P>
Total trade with the Maldives rose from 20.34 million U.S.
dollars in 1994 to 28.81 million dollars in 1996, representing a
growth of 40 percent in two years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
