<TEXT>
<P>
Rome, May 30 (Xinhua)-- Italy today named Manfredo Incisa de
Camarena new ambassador in Albania to replace its controversial
ambassador Paolo Foresti.
</P>
<P>
Paolo Foresti has been appointed to the position of Italy's
permanent representative in the Western European Union in Brussels.
</P>
<P>
Foresti served in Tirana for four years, and earlier this month
he was embroiled in a controversy after opposition parties accused
him of favoring President Sali Berisha.
</P>
<P>
An Opposition newspaper has published a transcript of a
telephone conversation between Foresti and Tritan Shehu, leader of
President Sali Berisha's Democratic Party, saying Foresti gave
advice on how to keep the president in office and urged Shehu not
to sign a deal brokered by Franz Vranitzky, envoy of the
Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe.
</P>
<P>
However, Foresti denied he had made such remarks. 
