<HEADLINE> Chongqing to Hold Three Gorges Tourism Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The third Three Gorges
International Tourism Festival, one of the major activities for
China's '97 Tourist Year, will be held in Chongqing from June 3 to
7.
</P>
<P>
The activity, jointly sponsored by the China National Tourism
Administration and Chongqing Municipal Government, will be the
city's first large-scale international activity since it became
China's fourth municipality in March.
</P>
<P>
A section of the Three Gorges in the Yangtze River, known for
its giant water-control project, is located in Chongqing,
southwest China.
</P>
<P>
"The tourism festival will help develop the area's rich tourism
resources and promote the city's popularity both at home and
abroad," said Xu Zhongmin, vice-mayor of the city.
</P>
<P>
During the festival, businessmen from the United States,
France,. Japan, Singapore, Malaysia, Tailand, Hong Kong, Taiwan
and other countries and regions will attend the activities in
Chongqing.
</P>
<P>
Beginning this year, the city will hold the festival
bi-annually, according to an official with the city's tourism
administration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
