<HEADLINE> Spain Intercepts Half European Cocaine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Spanish customs in 1996 seized a
total of 13.7 tons of cocaine, accounting for 50 percent of the
total cocaine seized in all European countries, Spanish police
said today.
</P>
<P>
Police also announced the arrest of two people at Madrid
airport, one a Spaniard and the other a Colombian, suspected of
smuggling 20 kilograms of cocaine from Colombia.
</P>
<P>
Spain has been regarded by traffickers as one of important
transfer stations where American drugs could be taken into
Europe. 
</P>
