<HEADLINE> Summer Camp On "the Roof of the World" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- A summer camp on "the roof of the
world" for Chinese college students will be held in Lhasa, capital
of the Tibet Autonomous Region, from July 31 to August 13.
</P>
<P>
Its theme is "scaling the peak of the science world and probing
the secrets of 'the roof of the world'", according to the
Commission for the Integrated Survey of Natural Resources of the
Chinese Academy of Sciences.
</P>
<P>
Southwest China's Qinghai-Tibet Plateau is the highest in the
world, at an average of 4,000 meters above sea level. The unique
environment, rich natural resources and interesting Tibetan
culture have attracted scientists worldwide.
</P>
<P>
The summer camp is being sponsored by the China Qinghai-Tibet
Plateau Society, the All China Students' Federation, the
government of the Tibet Autonomous Region, and Hong Kong
University. 
</P>
</TEXT>
