<HEADLINE> Thailand to Import 240,506 Tons of Rice This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Thailand will import 240,506 tons
of rice this year as part of its market opening commitment to the
World Trade Organization, according to Thai Commerce Minister
Narongchai Akrasanee.
</P>
<P>
The imports are made in two periods: 114,241 tons between May
and August, and 126,265 tons from September to December.
</P>
<P>
If import applications exceed the import quota for each period,
allocations will be considered and rights will not be
transferable, Narongchai was quoted today by the local press as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Thailand is the world's leading rice exporter.  
</P>
