<HEADLINE> Sampras, Novotna Beaten at French Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Following the elimination of
fifth-seed Thomas Muster, world number one and top-seeded Pete
Sampras and women's fourth seed Jana Novotna were also show the
exit at the French Open on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Sampras failed once again in his quest to win the only major
title missing from his collection as he lost to Magnus Norman of
Sweden 6-2, 6-4, 2-6, 6-4 in the third round.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on Friday, clay court expert Muster was beaten by
20-year-old Brazilian Gustavo Kuerten in five sets.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Yevgeny Kafelnikov beat Cedric Pioline, the
top player of France, also in five sets. Andrei Medvedev of
Ukraine also beat a French player in the third round.
</P>
<P>
In the women's singles, Jana Novotna crashed out to
87th-ranked Nicole Arendt of the United States 3-6, 6-4, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
The number-15 seed Karina Habsuova of Slovakia was also beaten
in straight sets by Ruxandra Dragomir of Romania.
</P>
<P>
Steffi Graf and 11th-seeded Amanda Coetzer both advanced and
moved one step closer to a possible quarter-final clash. 
</P>
</TEXT>
