<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Philippine Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading Philippine newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Manila Bulletin
</P>
<P>
-- Share prices on the Philippine Stock Exchange rose for the
seventh straight day Friday after a less dismal-than-expected
gross national product growth and government assurances of
achieving its annual target.
</P>
<P>
The Manila Times
</P>
<P>
-- Manila and Washington are back to square one in negotiations
for the resumption of joint military exercise, after both sides
agreed to scrap earlier versions of a proposed Status of Forces
Agreement.
</P>
<P>
Today
</P>
<P>
-- Philippine President Fidel Ramos said Friday he is satisfied
with the 6.1 percent growth of the gross national product for the
first quarter of the year, although it fell short of the
government's projected 6.4 percent and is much lower than last
year's 6.9 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
