<HEADLINE> Norway Beats Brazil 4-2 in Soccer Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, May 30 (Xinhua) -- World champion Brazil suffered a
rare defeat sinch 1994 World Cup as it lost to Norway 4-2 in a
soccer friendly at Oslo on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Tore Andr Flo scored twice for Norway while Petter Rudi and
Egil Ystenstad added the other two goals.
</P>
<P>
Flo scored at the 17th and 33rd minutes to put Norway 3-1 ahead
at halftime.
</P>
<P>
Ystenstad, who sutstituted for Rudi after the interval, sealed
the 4-2 victory for Norway.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian superstar Ronaldo was held scoreless in the match
played before 21,799 local fans.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian team will go to France to take part in the
four-nation soccer tournament which also attracts the
participation of France, England and Italy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
