<HEADLINE> Three Chinese Pairs Enter Women's Doubles Semis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GLASGOW, Scotland, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Three Chinese women's
doubles pairs entered the semi-finals of the world championships
here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Top seed and Olympic champions Ge Fei and Gu Jun swept past
sixth-seeded Rikke Olsen and Helene Kirkegaard of Denmark 15-2,
15-8 in 25 minutes to set up a semi-final clash against
compatriots Qian Hong and Liu Lu, who defeated Indonesia's Denyana
Lomban and Indarti Isoliana 15-10, 15-6.
</P>
<P>
Tang Yongshu and Qin Yiyuan rallied from one game down to beat
European champions Marlene Thomsen and Lisbet Stuer-Lauridsen of
Denmark 7-15, 15-8, 15-1.
</P>
<P>
They will meet All England runners-up Eliza and Rosiana Zelin
from Indonesia, who rolled over Malaysia's unseeded pair Chor Hooi
Yee and Lim Pek Siah 15-6, 15-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
