<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Stars Feature Super-Long Relay to Mark HK's Handover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 31 (Xinhua) -- A month-long marathon-style relay
race from Hong Kong up to the Chinese capital Beijing, which
starts on Sunday, will mark Hong Kong's return to China, it was
announced here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Among the participants of the super-long relay are some ace
athletes from both Hong Kong and the Chinese mainland, including
national and world champions and Olympic gold medalists.
</P>
<P>
China's table tennis world champion and Olympic gold medalist
Deng Yaping and her title-winning teammates lead a golden team
which consists of such stars as world record holder and
long-distance runner Wang Junxia, former Asian and world champion
walker Xu Yongjiu and Asian triple jump record holder Zou
Zhenxian.
</P>
<P>
The relay will kick-off at a special ceremony at the Wanchai
Playground here on Sunday. It will be followed by a cross-over by
some 50 runners at the Huanggang check point of Shenzhen and a
ceremony in the city's indoor stadium later on the same day.
</P>
<P>
Participants of the relay will run a total of 11 stages at Hong
Kong and Chinese cities of Guangzhou, Changsha, Wuhan, Shanghai,
Nanjing, Zhengzhou, Jinan and Tianjin before reaching the
destination of Beijing, where a grand ceremony has been scheduled
in the Workers' Indoor Stadium.
</P>
<P>
Chinese officials of the local governments, celebrities and
representatives of athletes from clubs subordinate to the Hong
Kong Amateur Athletic Association (HKAAA) will join in the relay
at various stages.
</P>
<P>
The event is jointly organized by the Chinese Athletic
Association and the HKAAA. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
