<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysians Advances into Men's Doubles Semis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GLASGOW, Scotland, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Yap Kim Hock and Cheah
Soon Kit of Malaysia defeated Jon Holst-Christensen and Michael
Sogaard to enter the last four of the men's doubles event at the
world badminton championships here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Yap and Cheat, who lost to the Danish pair at the All England
Open semi-finals this March, took revenge with a 15-12, 15-12
victory.
</P>
<P>
They will take on Indonesia's Olympic gold medalists Rexy
Mainaky and Ricky Subagja, who disposed of Nikolaj Zuev and
Andreij Antropov of Russia 15-10, 15-10.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Indonesia's Budiarto Sigit and Candra Wijaya won
18-16, 15-2 over Thomas Stavngaard and Jim Laugesen of Denmark.
</P>
<P>
They takes on Lee Dong Soo and Yoo Yong Sung, South Korea's
only semi-finalists in all five events.
</P>
<P>
Lee and Yoo, ranked 14th in the world, weathered through a
75-minute battle to beat Sweden's Peter Axelsson and Par Gunnar
Jonsson 17-16, 17-14. 
</P>
</TEXT>
